Ellie's Boxes of Hope creates boxes filled with essential items for adults, comfort items for kids and even supplies for pets, designed based on real needs from families and first responders. These free care packages will help bring relief and encouragement to those facing unexpected tragedy and empower our firefighters to offer not just emergency response, but a message of hope when it\u2019s needed most. volunteers from across the Southeast are making a difference right here in Panama City! Through a partnership with the City\u2019s Community Redevelopment Agency (CRA) and the faith-based World Changers program, selected neighborhoods in the Millville and Downtown North districts are receiving free home improvements, from painting to porch repairs.\n\nEach year, the CRA identifies areas in need, accepts applications, and verifies homes and projects that qualify. The CRA funds materials, and World Changers provides the labor. More than 15 homes are being transformed this week, and the impact will last far beyond summer.\n\nThe City of Panama City's CRA is grateful for its partnership with World Changers and some local churches, which are not only completing these repairs but also taking care of the volunteers. These volunteers are working hard in this summer heat and are doing a wonderful job making a lasting impact in our community.
